RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHATWASITHINKING quickly opened a clear lead, saved ground setting the pace, drifted out slightly leaving the three-sixteenths pole and drew off to win with something left. BOB'S SNIPER prompted the pace while racing two-wide, was unable to reach the winner but finished well for second in a steady effort. MILEYS BLUECAT saved ground while being allowed to settle, angled out to be four-wide at the three-sixteenths pole and finished in a mild rally. CLAYTON DELANEY was unhurried early, came five-wide into the stretch and improved his position during the drive. WARFRONT FIGHTER saved ground chasing the pace but lacked a rally. FAMOUS ROCK STAR was forwardly placed for a half mile while racing three-wide and tired.

TYCHE AWAITS YOU saved ground while being reserved off the pace, came four-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. DONTFORGETHESUGAR saved ground prompting the early pace and tired.

LAKER JET bobbled at the start to get away behind her field, then was unhurried, came four-wide into the stretch and gained her best stride too late. MOSCOW LADY saved ground chasing the pace, lacked room while in tight nearing the quarter pole, angled out to split rivals nearing the three-sixteenths pole and finished willingly when clear. YELLEN prompted the early pace while racing two-wide and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 7 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE FEBRUARY 25, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 25, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500 (Claiming Races For $3 ,200 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BENNY THE JET saved ground stalking the pace, angled out to be three-wide at the quarter pole, caught PROUD LION at the eighth pole and proved narrowly best in a stiff drive. PROUD LION saved ground setting the pace, responded when challenged and held on gamely to lose a tough decision. R B EYE saved ground while being unhurried, slipped through entering the stretch and finished in a mild rally. FREESTONE was in tight along the inside entering the first turn then was reserved off the pace while racing thre-wide, came five-wide into the stretch and went evenly late. STATE OF THE UNION hopped at the start to get away behind his field then dropped back, moved up two-wide on the turn, split rivals nearing the quarter pole but lacked a late response. PLAYOFF BOUND prompted the pace while racing two-wide, was three-wide nearing the quarter pole and gave way. THE TRAINER OF FREESTONE LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST BENNY THE JET AND PROUD LION FOR INTERFERENCE ENTERING THE FIRST TURN, BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS THE STEWARDS MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.
